<p>At last I found the Ruby/GTK2 method: <a href="http://ruby-gnome2.sourceforge.jp/hiki.cgi?cmd=view&amp;p=Gtk%3A%3AWidget&amp;key=modify_bas#modify_base">Gtk::Widget#modify_base</a>.<p />Then I could implemented <strong>state</strong> method for Green Shoes. Look at <a href="https://github.com/ashbb/green_shoes/blob/master/snapshots/sample55.png">sample55</a> which is the same as <a href="http://shoes-tutorial-note.heroku.com/html/00526_The__state_style.html">this</a>. ;-)<p />Have fun,<br />ashbb</p>]]></content:encoded>
